# Theme Surface Contract

## The Rule

Page and container shell backgrounds MUST use `var(--surface-base)`.
Elevated cards/panels inside those shells use `var(--surface-card)` or `var(--surface-elevated)`.

```
--surface-base   → #000000 (dark) / #FFFFFF (light)  ← page shells, outermost containers
--surface-card   → #000000 (dark) / #FFFFFF (light)  ← cards, panels, modals
--surface-elevated → #101828 (dark) / #F1F5F9 (light) ← tooltips, dropdowns, nested panels
```

## Correct Examples

```tsx
// Page shell background
<div style={{ background: 'var(--surface-base)' }}>

// Card inside the shell
<div style={{ background: 'var(--surface-card)', border: '1px solid var(--border-default)' }}>

// Tailwind equivalent
<main className="bg-[var(--surface-base)]">
  <section className="bg-[var(--surface-card)]">
```

## Forbidden Patterns

```tsx
// NEVER hardcode dark hex backgrounds in components
background: '#000000'       // use var(--surface-base)
background: '#000'          // use var(--surface-base)
background: '#0C1220'       // use var(--surface-card)
background: '#0A1628'       // use var(--surface-card) or var(--surface-section)
backgroundColor: '#0d1424'  // use var(--surface-card)

// NEVER use Tailwind arbitrary hex for dark backgrounds
className="bg-[#0C1220]"   // use bg-[var(--surface-card)]
className="bg-[#000000]"   // use bg-[var(--surface-base)]
className="bg-black"        // use bg-[var(--surface-base)]
className="dark:bg-[#0b1426]" // use bg-[var(--surface-base)]

// NEVER use --surface-card for page-level containers
<main style={{ background: 'var(--surface-card)' }}>  // use --surface-base
```

## Allowed Exceptions (must be in exception registry)

- Overlays: `rgba(0,0,0,0.x)` for modal backdrops and image fades
- Gradients: `linear-gradient(...)` when blending for visual effects (e.g., hero fades)
- Token definition files: `globals.css`, `semantic-tokens.ts`, `verdict-design-tokens.ts`
- PDF/report generation: server-side rendering with fixed colors
- Third-party overrides: `.pac-container` (Google Places) and similar

## When Adding Container Backgrounds

1. Ask: "Is this a page shell or outermost wrapper?" → `var(--surface-base)`
2. Ask: "Is this a card or panel inside a shell?" → `var(--surface-card)`
3. Ask: "Is this nested inside a card?" → `var(--surface-elevated)`
4. Run `npm run theme:check` before committing
